The paper discusses the application of software-defined networking (SDN) and network virtualization in optical access networks, which are typically studied in the computer science sub-category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the architecture and protocols used in these networks, which are typically studied in the computer science sub-category of robotics (cs.RO) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses quality of service and multilayer networking, which are typically studied in the computer science sub-categories of communication (cs.COMM) and systems and control (cs.SY).
